Docs.example:
The following example attaches a handler to the  event, and checks the provided argument to determine
if there was an error:


connection.Closed += (exception) =>
{
    if (exception == null)
    {
        Console.WriteLine("Connection closed without error.");
    }
    else
    {
        Console.WriteLine($"Connection closed due to an error: {exception}");
    }
};

The following example attaches a handler to the  event, and checks the provided argument to log the ConnectionId.


connection.Reconnected += (connectionId) =>
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Connection successfully reconnected. The ConnectionId is now: {connectionId}");
};

The following example attaches a handler to the  event, and checks the provided argument to log the error.


connection.Reconnecting += (exception) =>
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Connection started reconnecting due to an error: {exception}");
};
